cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric objects (disks) and their intersections in the plane. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a tool to efficiently compute the ply number of a given drawing. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the ply number is a discrete parameter of a graph drawing. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper deals with visual representations of graphs. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper presents an interactive tool for exploring and improving the ply number.
